gs><font color=#FFFFFF>Author</font></td><td valign=top background=http://www.cafenet.plus.com/The_Magicians_Tower/Images/Background_1.gif class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=soulpyre>SoulPyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(11/26/02 6:23:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7981.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Magician for me?</span><hr size=1>  I cant decide on a caster class to play.  I've narrowed down to the magician and wizard and leaning towards the magician.  I mages can put out some sick damage with the pet and their spells.  Wizards from my understanding some kind of lacking for the first 48 levels then get better at 49.  Yet, i have heard some real negative things about magicians at later levels...does it really get bad?  Overall I just want a fun and powerful class to play...is the mage for me or is it the wizard? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=civin>Civin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#333333>(11/26/02 6:46:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7981.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Magician for me?</span><hr size=1> highend mage game - coh bitch..<br>
there are alot of stereotypes about mages that we dont have high dps / etc from the 'old' days that simply just are not true anymore. More and more people ARE coming to understand that but its a long uphill battle until we will be recognized for the dps our pets / our nukes / our ds's truely do when stacked together =) As I hit 60 I had honestly met less and less of this, especially with POP coming out there seems to be more of an acceptance of high end magicians but there are still many who think we just sit there and do nothing <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  but... if things pregress as they are now... we are looking much better then we used to to have in a group.  <p>-x- Xegony -x-----------------<br>
