You dont have to carry a sword to be a Warrior...</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jochangaladar>Jochan Galadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 764<br> <font color=#333333>(11/27/02 5:28:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7981.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Magician for me?</span><hr size=1> I'm obviously biased, but when I look for folks to fill in spots in a group I hit up other magicians first.  I understand the class, and I understand magicians who have logged out with their lfg flag still on.  I just do my part to help promote the class.  I like to think I do a good job at it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=artulyn1>Artulyn1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 228<br> <font color=#333333>(11/27/02 5:37:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7981.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Magician for me?</span><hr size=1> Mages can solo fairly well thru level 61, check the Things to Kill section of the Tower to see where the good solo spots are. The lack of defensive abilities kinda sucks, basically it's kill the critter, gate or die. However with the addition of new pet heals and summoned focii, we can do it alot easier than we did in the past. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
50+ wizards can quad kite once they get snare and have alot more defensive options like evacs and DAs but there are alot more places a mage can solo than there are good places to quad kite. <p>Artulyn Starsummoner Arch Mage<br>
<br>
For the light of a candle to be seen, it must be taken to a dark place. -- UKLG</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wezloc@themagicianstower>WEZLOC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1312<br> <font color=#333333>(11/27/02 7:57:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7981.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Magician for me?</span><hr size=1> Mages rock now. Our damage is probably the highest of any class right now post 60. Lvling as a mage from 1 to 50 is cake. We do struggle a bit from 51 to around 56. However at 57 things get alot easier and solo to 60 isn't to bad. Post 61 alot of solo options are gone but our group ability is alot higher at those levels. I would say if you want to group and solo mages are a better option then wizards. Also mages duo well with healers so that is another plus.<br>
<br>
Wezloc <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=krilenspiritlink>Krilen Spiritlink</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 551<br> <font color=#333333>(11/27/02 8:21:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7981.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Magician for me?</span><hr size=1> Mages do sort of in between realms of damage. We can sustain good damage, and as casters do good burst damage. I find i'm getting more and more well received into pickup groups in the 60+ game. A mage's burst dps is okay, but a mage really doesn't have anything to my knowledge to make an uber guild would want to recruit more than a handful of them.<br>
<br>
Until you start to get FT, AAs, and especially a clicky nuke item, wizards honestly aren't anything to write home about in groups, however they make up for that in solo capability at later levels (but beware the poor soloing abilities at low levels before you can quad). A wizard's burst DPS is higher than a mage's, and burst seems to be important from what i read about 60+ PoP encounters. I'd think an uber guild would welcome quite a lot of wizards before they decide they're overrun.<br>
<br>
Neither class is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>really</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> better. I hope you choose the one which works right for you. <p>Happy trails.</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=krilenspiritlink>Krilen Spiritlink</A> at: 11/27/02 8:21:46 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=soulpyre>SoulPyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#333333>(11/27/02 6:50:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7981.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Magician for me?</span><hr size=1> Appreciate all the responses so far.  My friend my start a new char to duo with me...any thoughts on what would go good with a mage or wiz? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=braxxxus02>Braxxxus02</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 100<br> <font color=#333333>(11/27/02 6:56:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7981.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Magician for me?</span><hr size=1> Kind of depends.  If you were going to both try to get into groups then...<br>
<br>
Cleric, Enchanter, Shaman<br>
<br>
If you were just going to duo experience grind with a mage then . . .<br>
<br>
Mage, Cleric, Necro, Enchanter might be some good options.<br>
But, I am sure there are many good possibilities.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gamrok>Gamrok</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 369<br> <font color=#333333>(11/29/02 12:53:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7981.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Magician for me?</span><hr size=1> Mage + Shaman.. you can duo to 65. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=8548" target="top">Gamrok Lazyarse</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Arch Mage not of <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub70.ezboard.com/bentropy27363" target="top">Sigil</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dolekinsoothesayer>Dolekin Soothesayer</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.soldiers-of-light.net/phpBB2/images/avatars/gallery/Misc3/babykick.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#333333>(11/29/02 1:32:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7981.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Magician for me?</span><hr size=1> The convience of being a mage is that you get your choice of soloing or grouping.  If you only have an hour to kill, you can hop on and go soloing for a bit and log off.  Instead of being faced to find a group, and spend most of your time LFG.  <br>
<br>
I really enjoy being a mage because I have the choice whether to be independent or dependent.  At some levels, because of what spells, pets, and mobs you can fight: its in your interest to group.<br>
<br>
Mage class has its frustrations at times, but too me it has too many pluses to pass mages by.  It also has a lot of goals built into it: get __ level to get X pet, get level 49 for the uber pets, get your epic for the super uber pets, ding 55 for CoTH, ding 60 for group DS, and list grows. <p>&lt;p&gt;&lt;div align=left&gt;&lt;table width=&quot;270&quot; border=&quot;1&quot; bgcolor=&quot;000000&quot; cellpadding=&quot;5&quot;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;DIV style=&quot;FILTER: glow(color=FFFF00); WIDTH: 100%; POSITION: relative&quot; align=center&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Georgia, Times New Roman, Times, serif&quot; size=&quot;5&quot; color=&quot;#000000&quot;&gt;&lt;I&gt;&lt;a style=&quot;font-weight:bold; color:#FFFF00; text-decoration: none&quot;href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=43987 &gt;Dolekin Soothesayer&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/I&gt;&lt;DIV style=&quot;FILTER:  Blur(Add = 1,Direction=225, Strength=20); WIDTH: 100%; POSITION: relative&quot; align=center&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot; color=&quot;CCCCCC&quot;&gt;Gnomish Conjurer of the 58th Season&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr bgcolor=#dcdeed&gt;&lt;td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left&gt;<br>
<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zeem@themagicianstower>Zeem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 480<br> <font color=#333333>(11/29/02 2:15:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7981.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  DPS...</span><hr size=1> Then it come to DPS ...  Mages are maybe the best. Rogues can come close, then it come to sustained dmg.<br>
<br>
Mage+Shaman is probaly the single best duo combo in the game, maybe a cleric+Chanter will be better if they find something good to charm.<br>
